AB  - The paper outlines an open economy version of the Lucas competitive equilibrium rational expectations model. It analyses the determination of output, prices, exports, imports and the exchange rate under fixed and floating exchange rate regimes where information on the current exchange rate is used to infer the current values of foreign and domestic monetary shocks. Output is influenced by both foreign and domestic monetary shocks but independent of systematic foreign and domestic monetary growth under both exchange rate regimes. Flexible exchange rates insulate the domestic economy from systematic foreign monetary growth.
