UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/002219968490045X
AB  - This paper develops a model of trade in monopolistically competitive commodities of the type analysed by Krugman and by Dixit and Norman. It is established that small perturbations in the parameters of the model radically change the number and type of equilibria of the model. For certain parameter values, the model has multiple equilibria, some, though possibly not all, of which support intra-industry trade. The stability of each equilibrium is examined, and it is established that if there are multiple equilibria, there are multiple stable equilibria.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Dynamic effects of protection on productivity
AU  - Bardhan, Pranab
AU  - Kletzer, Ken
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 16
IS  - 1
SP  - 45
EP  - 57
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/02/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(84)90042-4
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199684900424
AB  - In this paper we first show how the positive or negative effects of protection on modernization of the capital stock and hence on average labor productivity depend on the technological characteristics of the protected sector. We then introduce learning by doing and show that even when protection lengthens the economic life of capital, there is a dynamic trade-off between its initial productivity-depressing effect and the tariff-induced learning effect, and that after a determinable date the latter effect predominates on the time-path of productivity.
ER  - 
